title: G-Men Never Forget (1948) Old Time Serial (OTS)
description:
It's 1948 and the G-Men are on the case in glorious Black and White.  It takes them 12 episodes but they get their man....or men.  

Holy Double Take -- it's Clayton Moore!  You mean he did something BEFORE becoming the Lone Ranger?  Yes, Tonto, HE DID!

Escaped criminal Victor Murkland kidnaps the police commissioner and with the aid of plastic surgery, takes his place. Federal Agent O'Hara is called from Washington to try to stop the wave of crime initiated by Murkland not knowing that he is pretending to be the police commissioner and is aware of O'Hara's every move. 

G-Man and a female detective sergeant pursue racketeers, unaware that her police commissioner is actually a gang boss altered by plastic surgery.

Directors: Fred C. Brannon, Yakima Canutt (I think I would change my name.)

Writers: Franklin Adreon, Basil Dickey (I KNOW I would change that name!  Tasty?)

Stars: Clayton Moore, Roy Barcroft, Ramsay Ames
